  "prompt": "I feel embarassed for not having a car. What should I do?",
  "response": "Here are some thoughts to help you:\n\n1. Remember that transportation is a personal choice\n- Public transit\n- Biking\n- Walking\n- Ridesharing\n\n2. Financial perspective\n- Not having a car can save money on:\n- Car payments\n- Insurance\n- Maintenance\n- Gas\n- Parking\n\n3. Alternative transportation options\n- Public transportation\n- Bike\n- Scooter\n- Carpooling\n- Rideshare services\n- Car rental when needed\n\n4. Shift your mindset\n- Your worth isn't determined by owning a car\n- Focus on your other strengths and achievements\n- Many people choose not to own a car\n\n5. Long-term planning\n- Save money\n- Improve credit\n- Work towards car ownership if desired\n\n6. Practical steps\n- Budget for future car purchase\n- Build savings\n- Research affordable car options\n- Consider used vehicles\n\nRemember: There's no reason to feel embarrassed. Transportation is a personal choice, and everyone's situation is different.",
